        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3394194209" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16714375825715050002">A poetic Love book. This is Devine.<br/><br/>Love is the only freedom in the world because it is so elevates the spirit that the laws of humanity and the phenomena of nature do not alter its course. <br/><br/>Khalil Gibran was 18 years old when he fell in love with a beautiful woman named Selma. He was introduced to her by her father Farris Effandi who was an old friend to his Father .<br/>Selma lost her father when she was an infant and her father was the richest man in the country, he loved Selma more than anything el</span>
  <span id="freeText16714375825715050002" style="display:none">A poetic Love book. This is Devine.<br /><br />Love is the only freedom in the world because it is so elevates the spirit that the laws of humanity and the phenomena of nature do not alter its course. <br /><br />Khalil Gibran was 18 years old when he fell in love with a beautiful woman named Selma. He was introduced to her by her father Farris Effandi who was an old friend to his Father .<br />Selma lost her father when she was an infant and her father was the richest man in the country, he loved Selma more than anything else in this world.<br /><br />But the Bishop of the country played his wicked plan. The Bishop had a nephew and he wanted him to marry Selma so that the Bishop could acquire Farris Effandi's wealth. <br /><br />But one fine day as of the holy spirits Selma and Gibran fell in love with each other knowing that their destiny was not meant to be together.. <br /><br />Months passed and as per Bishops evil plan , Selma got married to his nephew , Although her Father didn't wish her to marry Bishop's nephew...<br /><br />After few months of marriage her Father died due to illness and Gibran became her only person to her sorrow..<br /><br />Gibran and Selma met each other once in a month. In a temple where they shared their love, sorrow and misery..<br /><br />The Bishop came to know about this .. and Selma worried that her love will be in trouble.. So they ended their Meeting.<br /><br />Five years passed and her husband was treating her like a slave ... she wasn't able to bare a fruit from her...<br />But one day by God's grace she gave birth to a boy at dawn... but God had other plans the boy was born in the dawn and died in the sunrise... she was in great pain she embraced her son and hit herself against the wall.. By the end of the day there were two bodies lying on the ground.<br /><br />She was buried embracing her son and upon her Father's ditch. <br /><br />Simply innocent beautiful love story.🙂<br /><br />Metaphors are so Devine in this book... Beautiful comparison between the feelings and Nature.<br /><br />It is the most beautiful moment were people fell in love and they know they are in love but they don't confront each other they just gaze at each other in Silence.<br /><br />It is said that " That love is Delightful were the destiny isn't meant to be together "...<br /><br />The cup doesn't entice our lips unless the wines color is seen through the transparent crystal❤</span>
  <a data-text-id="16714375825715050002" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

