<div id="review_4023649461" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4023649461" />
    <a title="Sara Raquel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/104683913-sara-raquel"><img alt="Sara Raquel" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1631644725p2/104683913.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4023649461?book_show_action=true">Jun 15, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sara Raquel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sara Raquel" href="/user/show/104683913-sara-raquel">Sara Raquel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781979253185" href="/book/show/39333003-the-broken-wings">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4023649461" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10565285827054350293">The broken wings is a poetic novel, a tale of tragic love, set in Beirut, Lebanon. Gibran describes the passion and love of a young man for Selma, a young woman, who is forced into marriage with a man she doesn&apos;t love. It&apos;s a book about love, life, human existence, happiness and deals with many social issues of the time, such as religious corruption and the lack of women&apos;s rights. There&apos;s so much in this book. Although love is the focus, it&apos;s not only about love. <br/><br/>I cannot even begin to explain h</span>
  <span id="freeText10565285827054350293" style="display:none">The broken wings is a poetic novel, a tale of tragic love, set in Beirut, Lebanon. Gibran describes the passion and love of a young man for Selma, a young woman, who is forced into marriage with a man she doesn't love. It's a book about love, life, human existence, happiness and deals with many social issues of the time, such as religious corruption and the lack of women's rights. There's so much in this book. Although love is the focus, it's not only about love. <br /><br />I cannot even begin to explain how much I loved this book. No matter what I say, I will not do it justice. It's probably the book with the most beautiful writing I have ever read. I now want to read everything Gibran has ever written. I tabbed SO much and it still wasn't enough because I just wanted to tab every single paragraph. I just finished it and I already want to reread it and annotate. I just know that I will be rereading this book many times in the future.<br />I'm so overwhelmed by thoughts and feelings that it's very hard to clearly articulate why this book is so phenomenal.<br />It's a very short book. But I didn't speed through it. I read it very slowly, savoring every word. Sometimes I reread the same sentence three times so that it could have a bigger impact on me.<br />If you love poetic writing, character-driven books, short books with depth and tragedy, this one's for you! Please read it, I want every one to have the same beautiful experience.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10565285827054350293" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


